# Shared Package — Trellis Cross-Package Types & Schemas

## Purpose
`packages/shared` is the single source of truth for types, Zod schemas, constants, and enums used by mobile, web, and API. Changes here propagate everywhere via TypeScript inference and tRPC.

## Schema Organization
```
packages/shared/src/
├── schemas/              # Zod schemas (the source of truth)
│   ├── violation.ts
│   ├── assessment.ts
│   ├── payment.ts
│   ├── property.ts
│   ├── member.ts
│   ├── document.ts
│   ├── communication.ts
│   ├── arc.ts
│   ├── meeting.ts
│   └── common.ts         # Shared primitives (pagination, IDs, dates)
├── constants/
│   ├── roles.ts
│   ├── permissions.ts
│   ├── states.ts
│   └── violation-states.ts
├── types/
│   └── index.ts
└── utils/
    ├── currency.ts
    ├── date.ts
    └── validation.ts
```

## Rules
- Zod schema is the source of truth — derive TypeScript types with `z.infer<>`
- NEVER define a type manually if a Zod schema exists for it
- Schemas must be importable by both React Native and Node.js — no platform-specific code
- Use `z.discriminatedUnion()` for state-dependent shapes
- Use `z.coerce.date()` for date fields that come as strings from APIs
- Export both the schema and the inferred type from each file
- Keep schemas focused — one domain per file, compose with z.merge/z.extend
